    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Rinse your<strong> brown rice</strong>, add it to a pot with plenty of <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 20-25 min or until it's tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain, return it to the pot and keep covered until serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/warming-king-prawn-bhuna-with-brown-rice-and-naan/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and slice your<strong> brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Chop your<strong> cherry tomatoes</strong> in half, then peel and finely chop (or grate) your<strong> garlic</strong></p><p>Boil half a kettle</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/warming-king-prawn-bhuna-with-brown-rice-and-naan/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced onion </strong>with a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until starting to soften</p><p>Once softened, add the <strong>halved cherry tomatoes</strong> to the pan and cook for 4-5 min further or until starting to break down</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/warming-king-prawn-bhuna-with-brown-rice-and-naan/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, dissolve your<strong> vegetable stock mix</strong> and <strong>tomato paste</strong> in 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[260ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[340ml] </span><strong>boiled water </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>tomato</strong> <strong>stock</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/warming-king-prawn-bhuna-with-brown-rice-and-naan/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the tomatoes have broken down, add the<strong> chopped garlic</strong> to the pan with your <strong>garam masala</strong>,<strong> ground fenugreek</strong> and <strong>ground</strong> <strong>paprika</strong> and cook for 1 min further or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/warming-king-prawn-bhuna-with-brown-rice-and-naan/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Drain your <strong>king prawns</strong>, then add them to the pan with the <strong>tomato</strong> <strong>stock</strong> and cook for 6-7 min or until the prawns are cooked through and the sauce has thickened \u2013 this is your <strong>warming</strong> <strong>king prawn bhuna</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/warming-king-prawn-bhuna-with-brown-rice-and-naan/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the king prawns are cooking, chop your<strong> coriander</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Add your <strong>mini</strong> <strong>garlic & coriander naan[s]</strong> to a <strong>toaster</strong> for 1-2 min or until warmed through</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/warming-king-prawn-bhuna-with-brown-rice-and-naan/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>warming</strong> <strong>king prawn bhuna</strong> with the <strong>basmati rice</strong> and <strong>warmed</strong> <strong>naan</strong> to the side</p><p>Garnish with the <strong>chopped coriander</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
